
This single file, placed in the project's root directory, manages ignore rules for
both the 'frontend' (React) and 'backend' (Spring Boot) sub-folders.
--- GENERAL: IDE & SYSTEM FILES ---
Ignore files generated by IDEs and operating systems.
.idea/
.vscode/
*.iml
.project
.classpath
.settings/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.log

=======================================================================================
--- BACKEND: MAVEN / SPRING BOOT (Java) ---
All paths here are relative to the root folder.
=======================================================================================
The entire build output directory for the backend
backend/target/

VERY IMPORTANT: Ignore your secrets file to protect database credentials.
Create an "application.properties.example" file to show what's needed.
backend/src/main/resources/application.properties

=======================================================================================
--- FRONTEND: NODE / REACT / VITE ---
All paths here are relative to the root folder.
=======================================================================================
Dependency directories for the frontend
frontend/node_modules/

Build output directory for the frontend
frontend/dist/
frontend/build/

Vite-specific cache
frontend/.vite/

Environment variables - NEVER commit these to GitHub.
frontend/.env
frontend/.env.local
frontend/.env.*.local

Log files for the frontend
frontend/npm-debug.log*
frontend/yarn-debug.log*
frontend/yarn-error.log*
frontend/pnpm-debug.log*